        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 22 at 9:29PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 929 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles north of Guymon, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Guymon, Hooker, Goodwell, Tyrone, Optima, Hardesty, Eva, Hough,
Adams, and Baker.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Oklahoma.</instruction>
